In addition to the needed materials to produce the electrolyzer unit, different types of processes are required for each electrolyzer type. In this regard, the overall environmental impact will change if the type of electrolyzer changes. Figure 14 presents the procedure to manufacture the ALE to be combined into the proposed integrated design. In the first step, the Nickel powder should go through the rolling process followed by shaping to form the bipolar plates and electrodes. The Zirfon membrane can be also produced using the bathing and drying processes using N-Methyl-2-pyrrolidone (NMP), Polyphenylene Sulfide (PPS), Zirconium dioxide (Zr O2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
